    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Considerations for Storefront User Experience Customizations\n Configure the Default Storefront Pages\n Home Page\n Checkout Page\n My Account Page\n Product Compare Page\n Product Detail Page\n Product List Page\n Scaled Cart Page\n Configure Pagination Options for the Scaled Cart Page\n Options for Buyers to Sort and Search Items on the Scaled Cart Page\n Full Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page\n Localize the Last Refresh Timestamp on the Scaled Cart Page\n Partial Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page\n Unavailable Products on the Scaled Cart Page\n CSS Overrides for Cart Scale Components\n Shopping Cart Page\n Site Login Page\n Site Register Page\n Modify the Column Layout of a Storefront Page\n Add Widgets to Storefront Pages with Visualforce Components\n Customize Storefront Headings and Text with Page Labels\n Provide Intuitive Storefront Navigation with Menus\n Author Custom Content for a Storefront Page\n Style Your Storefront with a Theme\n Extend the Default Storefront Pages\n Source Options for Storefront Media\n Allow Only One Country, Territory, or State in Address Picklists\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nScaled Cart Page\n\nWhen you enable Cart Scale, the Scaled Cart page replaces the standard Shopping Cart page version 2.0 or 1.0. The Scaled Cart page provides enhancements for a buyer to manage a cart that contains a large number of items. A buyer can sort and search cart items, and browse cart items with pagination controls.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13) only\n\nUSER EXPERIENCE COMPATIBILITY\nInterface\tBootstrap 3 only\nUser visibility\tLogged-in users and guest users (depending on your storefront's guest user access)\nNOTE\nBy default, the Scaled Cart page uses the cc_tmpl_OneColRD template, which specifies a one-column page layout. For the best buyer experience with the Scaled Cart page, we recommend that you use the two-column layout. For more information, see:\nScale Your Cart Capabilities for a Large Number of Items\nModify the Column Layout of a Storefront Page\nThe Scaled Cart page respects many—but not all—configurations that apply to the Shopping Cart page version 2.0 or 1.0. Review the compatibility information listed for each Cart configuration or each option for the Shopping Cart page.\nConfigure Pagination Options for the Scaled Cart Page\nProvide an efficient, intuitive experience for a buyer who browses a large number of cart items on the Scaled Cart page. Customize the Scaled Cart page's default pagination controls so that a buyer can effectively navigate all items in the cart.\nOptions for Buyers to Sort and Search Items on the Scaled Cart Page\nBy default, the Scaled Cart page provides options for a buyer to search and sort all the items in the cart.\nFull Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page\nWith a large number of items in a cart, sometimes the price or availability of items throughout the cart can change when the buyer is finally ready to check out. To help ensure the quality of the cart data, the Scaled Cart page requires the buyer to execute a full refresh of the price and availability for all cart items. A buyer can also manually execute a full refresh at any time.\nLocalize the Last Refresh Timestamp on the Scaled Cart Page\nThe Scaled Cart page shows the date and time when the cart's prices were most recently refreshed. If your storefront supports multiple locales, you can localize the date and time format for a specific locale.\nPartial Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page\nWith a large number of items in a cart, repricing the entire cart for only minor changes in one paginated set of cart items can be expensive and unnecessary. Instead, the Scaled Cart page can execute a partial refresh after a buyer modifies the quantities of cart items on the current page.\nUnavailable Products on the Scaled Cart Page\nWhen a buyer refreshes the cart's data with either a full or partial refresh, the Scaled Cart page identifies products that are no longer available. Any unavailable products sort to the beginning of the cart items. The Scaled Cart page provides a few tools to help the buyer identify and remove unavailable products from the cart.\nCSS Overrides for Cart Scale Components\nThe Cart Scale components on the Scaled Cart page and Checkout page use default Bootstrap 3 CSS styles. To modify or hide these components in a custom theme, modify the appropriate CSS in your theme's styles.css file.\nSEE ALSO\nScale Your Cart Capabilities for a Large Number of Items\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
